JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says although there is much talk about radical economic transformation, it must not be used by certain families to line their pockets.He says if it doesn t eradicate poverty, it won't work.Ramaphosa -- who stepped in for President Jacob Zuma at Cosatu's central committee meeting -- received a standing ovation.WATCH: Ramaphosa addresses Cosatu meetingHe is the federation's preferred candidate for the ANC's top job. eNCA